<P>
OUTTAKES: WEIRD AL'S OSCAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By David Pecchia 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Is parodist Weird Al Yankovic in hot water with the Academy of Motion Picture 
Arts &amp; Sciences, which routinely takes action to prevent unauthorized use 
of Oscar's image? 
</P>
<P>
In his offbeat comedy, "UHF," due out Friday from Orion Pictures, Weird Al does 
an Indiana Jones "Raiders" send-up in one sequence -- scheming to steal a prop 
Oscar. 
</P>
<P>
Academy exec administrator Bruce Davis said the organization would wait until 
the film's release before considering legal action. 
</P>
<P>
Orion declined to comment, as did reps for Weird Al. David Pecchia 
</P>
</TEXT>
