<HEADLINE>
<P>
OUTTAKES: THE DEVIL, YOU SAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Leonard Klady 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Author-writer-director William Peter Blatty, currently completing Morgan 
Creek's "Exorcist: 1990," insists that his sequel will be "the last serious 
word on the subject." Meanwhile, his next project, "Demons 5, Exorcists 0," 
will send up the subject that made him a household name. 
</P>
<P>
"The script's completed, and Fox (which released '1990') has first refusal," 
said Blatty. "It's about a convention of priests beset by an evil presence." 
</P>
<P>
Then there's producer Steve Wizan's tentatively titled "Repossessed," a spoof 
written and directed by Robert Logan. It's about a woman -- played by 
"Exorcist" star Linda Blair, no less -- once possessed by a demon, who now 
seeks help when she feels that ole black magic returning. Leslie Nielsen is an 
off-kilter priest, Ned Beatty an evil evangelist and Morton Downey Jr. cameoed 
as a disbeliever. 
</P>
<P>
Wizan claims, "It's not an 'Exorcist' spoof. We're sending up all horror 
pictures. . . ." 
</P>
<P>
Blatty said he's aware of Wizan's project: "I hope it's fun. And I'm sure it's 
not at all like the film I'm preparing." Leonard Klady 
</P>
</TEXT>
