<HEADLINE>
<P>
INSIDE CAA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding "Inside the Agency," Michael Cieply's July 2 article about CAA, the 
Hollywood talent agency: 
</P>
<P>
The guys at Creative Artists do nothing all day but stroke people they like and 
"kill" people they don't like. They wield a ridiculous amount of power over the 
minds of an entire nation. 
</P>
<P>
Their power is derived not from ability or excellence or even intelligence. It 
comes simply from forming a coterie -- it's all "who you know." 
</P>
<P>
You can see why this sort of thing has such a negative effect on the Hollywood 
"product." In the case of CAA, they usually sacrifice artistic integrity for 
increased company profits. When they "package" a deal, putting the script, the 
actors and the director together, more often than not all of these "elements" 
are in-house. 
</P>
<P>
The game is money and power. The American public gets lousy programming as a 
result. 
</P>
<P>
RAY MASON 
</P>
<P>
Torrance 
</P>
