<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMERCIAL SCENE; 
</P>
<P>
PRUDENTIAL PLANS TO BUILD 18 BUILDINGS IN ONTARIO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Prudential Realty Group has purchased a 52-acre parcel adjacent to Ontario 
International Airport and plans to build an 18-building office and industrial 
complex on the site. 
</P>
<P>
Prudential reportedly paid the Lusk Co. more than $11 million for the parcel, 
which is inside the 1,855-acre California Commerce Center. Although plans are 
not yet completed, the buildings are expected to range from 40,000 to 125,000 
square feet each. 
</P>
<P>
Construction is expected to begin by August, and the first phase is scheduled 
for completion early next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
