Gunfire was reported in Somalia's capital of Mogadishu, but diplomats said the 
city appeared generally calm one day after clashes between religious worshipers 
and security forces left 23 people dead and 59 wounded. Police said the 
violence erupted when religious demonstrators attacked security forces. But 
witnesses said it appeared troops opened fire as Muslim worshipers left their 
place of prayer. 
