<P>
KILLING LAID TO POWER BATTLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police said the murder of a Hells Angels leader in a bloody barroom brawl in 
San Leandro last month may have been part of a power struggle between the 
motorcycle clan and an Aryan Brotherhood prison gang. Michael (Irish) 
O'Farrell, known to authorities as the No. 2 man in the Hells Angels, died in 
the bar fight on June 6. Aaron (Jerry) Marsh has been arrested in connection 
with the murder. Police said Marsh, identified as a member of the white 
supremacist-oriented Aryan Brotherhood, may have killed O'Farrell to gain 
status within his own organization. O'Farrell was repeatedly stabbed and shot. 
</P>
