<TEXT>
<P>
American Telephone &amp; Telegraph Co. said it will swap its 22% stake in 
Italian computer maker Olivetti for a large holding in Carlo de Benedetti's 
main industrial holding company. The announcement ends speculation that 
AT&amp;T would sell its Olivetti stake because of differences that emerged a 
year ago over the firms' industrial alliance formed in December, 1983. Under 
the new agreement, AT&amp;T is selling to De Benedetti's Italian holding firm 
Compagnie Industriali Riunite 100 million Olivetti shares at a price of $8.31 
each, for a total of $832 million. Then, AT&amp;T will buy 182.5 million CIR 
shares, also to total $832 million. 
</P>
