<P>
The executive director of the Public Utilities Commission in San Francisco is 
resigning next month. Victor Weisser, who has headed the PUC since 1986, is 
leaving to become president of the California Council for Environmental and 
Economic Balance, a private organization on environmental issues. As PUC 
director, Weisser supervised more than 1,000 people for the five-member 
commission that regulates rates and services of the state's privately owned 
energy, telephone, transportation and water companies. 
