<P>
Nicaragua's social development is on "the verge of disintegration" and Western 
powers should increase aid to the struggling Central American nation, Oxfam, a 
private British philanthropic agency, said. "The United States' embargo on 
trade with Nicaragua and unstable commodity prices have combined to cause 
economic collapse," Oxfam said in a publication marking the agency's 25 years 
of work in Nicaragua. Oxfam said it is appealing to the 12 Common Market 
nations to support peace moves in Nicaragua and to promote the disbanding and 
resettlement of the U.S.-backed Contras. 
