<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITIZENS GROUP TO MEET ON CONTROLLED GROWTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOP (Stop Those Old Politicians), a citizens group formed by Rancho Palos 
Verdes resident Joel Justin King, will hold a public meeting Wednesday at 7:30 
p.m. at the Peninsula Center Library, 650 Deep Valley Drive, Rolling Hills 
Estates. 
</P>
<P>
King said the group advocates city ordinances in Rancho Palos Verdes that would 
limit development, limit City Council terms to two years -- a matter that the 
California Court of Appeal recently ruled is preempted by state law -- and 
lower rates for cable television on the Palos Verdes Peninsula. 
</P>
