<P>
OPEN KITCHEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kathie Jenkins 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Someone's in the kitchen, as you can see. 
</P>
<P>
Brentwood Bar &amp; Grill, 11647 San Vicente Blvd., Brentwood. (213) 820-2121. 
Style: Grill with frills. Setting: Murmurs and money. Recommended dishes: 
Potato and onion tart; grilled shrimp with vegetable spaghetti; angel food 
sandwich. Cost per person, food only: $25-$45. 
</P>
<P>
Citrus, 6703 Melrose Ave., Los Angeles. (213) 857-0034. Style: 
California-French by L.A.'s premiere French pastry chef. Setting: Bright and 
airy with pretty garden patio that looks into the kitchen. Recommended dishes: 
Oyster mousse with beet sauce; grilled baby salmon; mille feuille with creme 
brulee. Cost per person, food only: $25-$60. 
</P>
<P>
Shane Hidden on the Glen, 2932 Beverly Glen Circle, Los Angeles. (213) 
470-6223. Style: Neighbhorhood pizza parlor to the stars. Setting: Alice in 
Southwesternland. Recommended dishes: Santa Fe chicken soup with ravioli; pizza 
with lamb sausage; beef quesadilla. Cost per person, food only: $12-$35. 
</P>
<P>
Tulipe, 8360 Melrose Ave., Los Angeles. (213) 655-7400. Style: French for the 
fun of it. Setting: Bright and noisy. Recommended dishes: Ravioli made of duck 
ham and snails in parsley coulis; blue cheese and pear pastry; smoked salmon on 
sauerkraut. Cost per person, food only: $20-$35. 
</P>
<P>
Victor Hugo's, 235 N. Beverly Dr., Beverly Hills. (213) 858-7292. Style: A 
lesson in the art of dining. Setting: Sleek and modern. Recommended dishes: 
Taramasalata; loin of lamb; tournedos of salmon. Cost per person, food only: 
$25-$40. Kathie Jenkins 
</P>
