<HEADLINE>
<P>
DISTRICT POWERS STOCK WEST ALL-STARS' ROSTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Putting players from powerhouses Woodland Hills West and Newhall-Saugus on the 
squad that will face the East team in today's American Legion District 20 
all-star game is like staging an all-star broadcast battle between Reagan and 
Scully: It just doesn't seem even. 
</P>
<P>
But take it from a partial observer: It's still a tough call to make. 
</P>
<P>
"The West may have more name recognition-type players," Newhall-Saugus Coach 
Tom Pedersen said, "but there are some pretty good ballplayers in the East, 
too." 
</P>
<P>
Newhall-Saugus (17-5) and Woodland Hills West (21-3) own the best records in 
the district and players from both are on what is a potentially explosive West 
team. The starting time for the game at Birmingham High is 1 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
"There's no real formula to it," District Commissioner Mel Swerdling said of 
how rosters are filled. "I just try to get as much exposure for as many players 
in the game as possible. It usually turns out pretty even." 
</P>
<P>
Woodland Hills West sends pitchers Pat Treend and Lance Gibson and its infield 
of Ryan McGuire (1B), Paul Geller (2B), Rick Banuelos (SS) and Del Marine (3B). 
</P>
<P>
Newhall-Saugus sends George Lopata (1B), Corey Byars (3B), Brad Anderson (SS) 
and Ben Ealy (OF). 
</P>
<P>
Panorama City, champion of the Eastern Division, will be represented on the 
East roster by five players: unbeaten right-handers Roland De La Maza (6-0) and 
Dave Unter (5-0), and Joe Cascione (2B), Shane Wight (SS) and Dave Garcia (OF). 
Sun Valley will be represented by the outfield trio of Shad Martinez, Herman 
Murillo and John Campbell. 
</P>
</TEXT>
