<HEADLINE>
<P>
NOMADS BEAT CONDORS, MOVE INTO FIRST IN WSL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The San Diego Nomads defeated the Arizona Condors, 4-0, Saturday night at 
Balboa Stadium to take sole possession of first place in the Western Soccer 
League. 
</P>
<P>
Thien Nguyen opened the scoring, followed by Mario Gonzalez, Steve Boardman and 
Paul Wright. Jerome Watson had three assists. 
</P>
<P>
The Nomads are 10-4, Arizona 4-11. The second-place Los Angeles Heat lost 
Saturday to the California Kickers, 1-0. 
</P>
