<TEXT>
<P>
Mike Rozier of the Houston Oilers agreed to a $5.45-million contract that will 
put him among the six highest-paid running backs in the National Football 
League, the Houston Post reported. 
</P>
<P>
Sources said the agreement was reached during a 10-hour negotiating session 
Friday in Washington. The Oilers said the deal has not been completed. 
</P>
<P>
The Post said Rozier will earn $850,000 this season, and his pay will increase 
from $900,000 in 1990 to $1.4 million in 1993. None of the contract is 
guaranteed, the newspaper said. 
</P>
