<HEADLINE>
<P>
TENNIS ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
AGASSI IS OUSTED BY GOMEZ IN U.S. PRO CHAMPIONSHIPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Top-seeded Andre Agassi was upset in the semifinals of the $415,000 U.S. Pro 
Tennis Championships Saturday night at Brookline, Mass., losing to Andres 
Gomez, 7-6 (7-1), 6-7 (7-3), 6-2. 
</P>
<P>
Agassi, 19 and ranked fourth in the world, lost for the second time in three 
matches against Gomez, an Ecuadorean ranked 27th. 
</P>
<P>
Gomez will meet Mats Wilander in tonight's final. Wilander beat Martin Jaite, 
3-6, 6-4, 6-4. 
</P>
<P>
Sixth-seeded Peter Lundgren of Sweden won two matches and advanced to the final 
of the $160,000 Volvo Hall of Fame tennis tournament at Newport, R.I. 
</P>
<P>
Lundgren defeated third-seeded John Fitzgerald of Australia, 7-6 (7-2), 7-6 
(7-4), in a morning match that had been suspended Friday with Lundgren leading, 
5-4. 
</P>
<P>
After a 2 1/2-hour break, Lundgren came back to beat Glenn Layendecker, 6-3, 
6-4. 
</P>
<P>
Lundgren will play unseeded Jim Pugh, a 6-4, 6-7 (7-4), 6-3 winner over Danie 
Visser of South Africa. 
</P>
<P>
Top-seeded Gabriela Sabatini of Argentina downed Katerina Maleeva of Bulgaria, 
6-3, 6-4, to reach the final of the $250,000 Gunze World tournament at Osaka, 
Japan. 
</P>
<P>
In today's final, Sabatini will play Mary Joe Fernandez, who beat Nana Miyagi 
of Japan, 6-1, 4-6, 7-5. 
</P>
<P>
Eighth-seeded Carl-Uwe Steeb of West Germany advanced to the final of the 
$305,000 Swiss Open with a 6-4, 5-7, 6-4 victory over Sergi Bruguera of Spain 
at Gstaad. 
</P>
<P>
In today's title match, Steeb will play unseeded Magnus Gustafsson of Sweden, 
who beat countryman Jan Gunnarsson, 6-4, 6-2. 
</P>
